00:32:49,190 --> 00:32:51,611
[SPEAKER_22]: It's wide enough to function as two lanes, and so it does

372
00:32:52,532 --> 00:33:02,264
[SPEAKER_22]: So what we're doing with the design is to kind of formalize the way that it's operating today, having this lane be a through and a left and the rights having this lane here.

373
00:33:03,265 --> 00:33:06,449
[SPEAKER_22]: But we also wanted to make sure we're providing a space for bicycles.

374
00:33:07,690 --> 00:33:19,056
[SPEAKER_22]: So we have the bike lane stay separated until about this point and then it can share the right turn lane with vehicles.

375
00:33:20,317 --> 00:33:26,400
[SPEAKER_22]: The reason we had to do this kind of shared scenario is because this right is a rather heavy movement.

376
00:33:27,221 --> 00:33:32,184
[SPEAKER_22]: We needed to have some storage area for the cars there and we just couldn't

377
00:33:32,944 --> 00:33:41,972
[SPEAKER_22]: come up with a safe geometry to have a separate bike lane kind of we call it in the pocket on its own between the through lane and the right turn lane.

378
00:33:43,613 --> 00:33:49,879
[SPEAKER_22]: So we, this was kind of a compromise here, but we wanted to make sure that we had this part separated here because

379
00:33:51,740 --> 00:33:56,261
[SPEAKER_22]: similar to what I was describing with the side-by-side lanes and the circle.

380
00:33:56,342 --> 00:34:05,504
[SPEAKER_22]: We don't want side-by-side lanes in the same direction approaching a crosswalk because you get what you call the multiple threat situation.

381
00:34:06,085 --> 00:34:12,887
[SPEAKER_22]: The drivers on the inside lane can block the view of drivers on the outside lane and pedestrians can get hurt that way.

382
00:34:13,087 --> 00:34:17,228
[SPEAKER_22]: So we wanted to make sure we have just the one drive lane and then the bike lane

383
00:34:18,888 --> 00:34:23,891
[SPEAKER_22]: with flex posts here to make sure that people can't go around, drivers can't go around a stopped vehicle.

384
00:34:25,693 --> 00:34:27,934
[SPEAKER_22]: We continue the southbound bike lane here.

385
00:34:28,214 --> 00:34:30,276
[SPEAKER_22]: We're able to preserve all of this parking here.

386
00:34:31,937 --> 00:34:39,482
[SPEAKER_22]: So I should say, I should note that this area does, this is the one area that did see some significant parking.

