1376
02:16:29,989 --> 02:16:42,998
[SPEAKER_20]: I think serious consideration needs to be taken here before we put those pylons up, which in the wintertime plowing, I can't imagine what that is going to do.

1377
02:16:43,568 --> 02:16:55,874
[SPEAKER_20]: Yes, we haven't had much snow this winter, but when we get the average amount of snow and the number of times that we must plow, this is a serious concern.

1378
02:16:56,214 --> 02:17:06,259
[SPEAKER_20]: And while I'm very aware of the crosswalk situations, yes, moving them back towards the houses a little bit will help.

1379
02:17:07,980 --> 02:17:12,822
[SPEAKER_20]: Reducing right lane turns into one lane only

1380
02:17:13,359 --> 02:17:17,521
[SPEAKER_20]: so that there can be a dedicated bicycle lane.

1381
02:17:19,242 --> 02:17:33,850
[SPEAKER_20]: While I have respect for bicyclists, it just does not make sense in a practical manner, because as I say, we have commuters, but we also have local residents that live here.

1382
02:17:33,890 --> 02:17:36,632
[SPEAKER_20]: And I thought the previous speaker, George, did a fine job.

1383
02:17:37,032 --> 02:17:38,092
[SPEAKER_20]: That's what I have to say.

1384
02:17:39,593 --> 02:17:40,794
[SPEAKER_20]: So please reconsider.

1385
02:17:45,435 --> 02:17:53,680
[SPEAKER_06]: Andrew, and briefly, I just wanted to touch upon, so as Amy pointed out, some of the cones that we have out there are called looper cones.

1386
02:17:54,140 --> 02:18:02,265
[SPEAKER_06]: We use those to try to decipher where the best place for a more permanent flex post that Amy described would be.

1387
02:18:03,106 --> 02:18:14,493
[SPEAKER_06]: So I imagine this area, we would start off, if we chose to do those, we'd start off with looper cones to determine the best place for those to be to accommodate

1388
02:18:15,129 --> 02:18:28,817
[SPEAKER_06]: box trucks buses or 18 wheelers and then and then they would that something more permanent will be positions as such once that's determined so that's the approach we took at Boston Avenue and High Street in West Medford.

1389
02:18:29,317 --> 02:18:31,819
[SPEAKER_06]: Those cones in that particular corner come from Arlington.

1390
02:18:32,499 --> 02:18:36,282
[SPEAKER_06]: They accommodate an 18 wheeler and a MBTA bus taking that right turn.

1391
02:18:36,342 --> 02:18:43,526
[SPEAKER_06]: So if we went out immediately and did the more permanent, the fixed ones and then a truck, we're not able to make the turn.

1392
02:18:44,389 --> 02:18:45,730
[SPEAKER_06]: And, you know, that would be a problem.

1393
02:18:45,750 --> 02:18:49,951
[SPEAKER_06]: So we do take a kind of incremental measured approach, if that helps.

1394
02:18:50,531 --> 02:18:57,013
[SPEAKER_10]: Yeah, that was kind of gonna be my next question was gonna be how if these are fixed, how is a truck, this is a truck route.

1395
02:18:58,374 --> 02:19:04,496
[SPEAKER_10]: And the only truck route that we have in this area, they're not allowed to drive on 16.

1396
02:19:04,576 --> 02:19:07,177
[SPEAKER_10]: So obviously, that would be a concern.

1397
02:19:07,417 --> 02:19:10,358
[SPEAKER_10]: This is the only route that they can go.

1398
02:19:10,378 --> 02:19:13,139
[SPEAKER_10]: And obviously, you had mentioned that

1399
02:19:14,614 --> 02:19:17,915
[SPEAKER_10]: that would be something that you guys have already taken into consideration.

1400
02:19:17,995 --> 02:19:25,538
[SPEAKER_10]: It's already an area in which you did, but that's kind of answered my question for me.

1401
02:19:28,099 --> 02:19:29,420
[SPEAKER_10]: George, you have your hand raised again.

1402
02:19:29,440 --> 02:19:32,141
[SPEAKER_10]: I'd like to speak on that since I don't speak.

1403
02:19:34,782 --> 02:19:35,282
[SPEAKER_10]: Go ahead, George.

1404
02:19:35,622 --> 02:19:36,042
[SPEAKER_04]: Yeah, sorry.

1405
02:19:36,102 --> 02:19:36,582
[SPEAKER_04]: I thought of you.

1406
02:19:36,822 --> 02:19:38,443
[SPEAKER_04]: So just one quick question on maintenance now.

1407
02:19:38,503 --> 02:19:44,045
[SPEAKER_04]: So if you put those flex cones in and Winthrop Street is cleaned once a week in summer,

1408
02:19:44,718 --> 02:19:55,024
[SPEAKER_04]: Can the sweet sweepers get on the other side or is all this debris going to build up between the flex posts and my house and I'm going to be out there sweeping it myself because you can't sweep it.

1409
02:19:55,504 --> 02:20:03,348
[SPEAKER_04]: You know, also like you said, when the winter comes and those things are stuck there, is it going to be this permanent mound of snow between the flex posts of my driveway?

1410
02:20:03,368 --> 02:20:07,531
[SPEAKER_04]: It's going to make it harder to get onto the street because the plows, where they went,

1411
02:20:08,155 --> 02:20:09,836
[SPEAKER_04]: pushing up those flex posts the whole way down.

1412
02:20:10,137 --> 02:20:13,419
[SPEAKER_04]: So, I mean, you gotta think of these are affecting people's where they live.

1413
02:20:13,479 --> 02:20:14,800
[SPEAKER_04]: This isn't the rotary.

1414
02:20:14,860 --> 02:20:16,121
[SPEAKER_04]: This isn't the park.

1415
02:20:16,482 --> 02:20:17,663
[SPEAKER_04]: This isn't the high school.

1416
02:20:18,023 --> 02:20:19,284
[SPEAKER_04]: This is residential.

1417
02:20:19,304 --> 02:20:21,806
[SPEAKER_04]: We live here where I've been here 33 years.

1418
02:20:21,846 --> 02:20:34,836
[SPEAKER_04]: This is my home, you know, and I feel proud of it and I just don't wanna feel like it's being trashed by this proposal because it's it doesn't look good and I don't think you thought about these other things that I'm gonna have to, you know, clean my own street now.

1419
02:20:35,577 --> 02:20:36,558
[SPEAKER_04]: It's, you know, it's

1420
02:20:37,284 --> 02:20:50,667
[SPEAKER_04]: It's a nice area, I think, I think the painting is what we're going to have to go with for aesthetics even incident and then that's a win win I mean we're, you get something but those posts I mean the parking is going to be difficult because

1421
02:20:51,435 --> 02:20:55,476
[SPEAKER_04]: people have multiple cars, but I mean, I absolutely can't live with those flex posts.

1422
02:20:55,696 --> 02:21:02,017
[SPEAKER_04]: I mean, it's, and I think it's going to affect if I want to sell my house, who wants to buy a house with those posts in front of you?

1423
02:21:02,237 --> 02:21:04,418
[SPEAKER_04]: You got to think about what it does to the people that live here.

1424
02:21:04,438 --> 02:21:07,658
[SPEAKER_04]: These are, it's, this isn't a commercial area, it's residential.

1425
02:21:08,358 --> 02:21:11,559
[SPEAKER_04]: And I just, I mean, no one's talked about that cleaning part, but that just popped into my head.

1426
02:21:12,359 --> 02:21:16,520
[SPEAKER_04]: You know, it's just one more thing that's going to be dumped on us because of this plan.

1427
02:21:18,935 --> 02:21:31,822
[SPEAKER_10]: HAB-Michael Leccesereeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeee

1428
02:21:48,503 --> 02:21:54,709
[SPEAKER_06]: It's really about the bike lane versus parking or things like that for this particular approval.

1429
02:21:55,189 --> 02:21:55,429
[SPEAKER_10]: Okay.

