[SPEAKER_10]: Thank you, Todd.

1431
02:21:56,330 --> 02:22:13,246
[SPEAKER_10]: Obviously I want to stay on track for what we're actually proposing and what we passed here tonight would be to reiterate what Todd said, whether or not these are painted lines, not a flex post, we're just, it's the parking spots for the bike lane.

1432
02:22:19,171 --> 02:22:23,637
[SPEAKER_06]: I will say it is valuable to hear from the community of their opinions about that.

1433
02:22:23,817 --> 02:22:25,319
[SPEAKER_06]: It's not going unnoticed.

1434
02:22:25,399 --> 02:22:29,184
[SPEAKER_06]: It just doesn't, you know, just trying to make that clarification.

1435
02:22:29,244 --> 02:22:29,525
[SPEAKER_06]: Thank you.

1436
02:22:30,897 --> 02:22:37,661
[SPEAKER_22]: I can respond briefly to the snow and street sweeping questions since that was the first time that was brought up.

1437
02:22:38,762 --> 02:22:40,923
[SPEAKER_22]: This is not a new problem.

1438
02:22:41,824 --> 02:22:52,270
[SPEAKER_22]: A lot of adjacent communities are figuring out how to deal with that with new different kinds of infrastructure, bike infrastructure that looks like this with flex posts sometimes, sometimes with curbs.

1439
02:22:52,990 --> 02:22:58,613
[SPEAKER_22]: And there are different types of machines that you can get that are smaller that will plow

1440
02:22:59,814 --> 02:23:00,734
[SPEAKER_22]: but they have a smaller width.

1441
02:23:01,395 --> 02:23:07,597
[SPEAKER_22]: We actually did get one of those machines recently that's made to be in smaller spaces.

1442
02:23:09,118 --> 02:23:20,682
[SPEAKER_22]: These types of things, the maintenance concerns are absolutely real concerns, but they are also things that are one, not unique that other cities have had to deal with and problems that can be solved.

1443
02:23:23,003 --> 02:23:26,905
[SPEAKER_22]: We're here to solve not just the design problems, but also the maintenance problems.

1444
02:23:29,656 --> 02:23:34,338
[SPEAKER_14]: Thank you.

1445
