[SPEAKER_19]: for a while.

1464
02:24:56,117 --> 02:25:04,768
[SPEAKER_19]: And just for some counterbalance I don't think pylons are ugly at all they reflect the entire concept of the complete streets community.

1465
02:25:06,049 --> 02:25:07,651
[SPEAKER_19]: And it's really just putting

1466
02:25:08,843 --> 02:25:20,066
[SPEAKER_19]: the needs or the interests of a few homeowners over a comprehensive bike network, which I would urge the committee not to do and to continue with this.

1467
02:25:20,206 --> 02:25:23,987
[SPEAKER_19]: It's entirely subjective to say that pylons are not attractive.

1468
02:25:24,507 --> 02:25:31,909
[SPEAKER_19]: They provide a huge benefit and a painted line is nowhere near a pylon or a protective bike lane.

1469
02:25:32,709 --> 02:25:33,050
[SPEAKER_19]: Thank you.

1470
02:25:35,170 --> 02:25:37,611
[SPEAKER_10]: Just to reiterate what Todd had said,

1471
02:25:38,641 --> 02:25:58,645
[SPEAKER_10]: making the motion or we're speaking on parking spaces for the bike lane, the pylons or traffic cones or not, that would be up to the commissioner for PPW and that to be reiterated.

1472
